<TITLE> BNP wants 'just' solution </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 25 (bdnews24.com) - BNP called for a 'just' solution to the bloody rebellion at BDR headquarters Wednesday. "We are calling on all the relevant sides to show patience and restraint to come to a just and logical solution to the problems," Maruf Kamal Khan, the chief of the party chairperson's information cell, told reporters at around 9pm. "The public have not been notified about the crisis by the government. However, what we have come to learn from different media outlets concerns us," he said. BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia came to her political office at around 7pm. She reviewed the day's incidents with senior party leaders, cancelling a standing committee meeting, said Khan. M Saifur Rahman, Khandaker Delwar Hossain, Dr. Khandaker Mosharraf Hossain, barrister Moudud Ahmed, Lt Gen (rtd) Mahbubur Rahman, Salahuddin Quader Chowdhury barrister Jamir Uddin Sarcar, MK Anwar were present among others. bdne
